The paper deals with the algorithmic problem of community detection in networks, which is a topic that falls under several CS sub-categories. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category since the paper discusses the complexity of algorithms for community detection. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category since the paper deals with detecting communities in friendship graphs. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category since the paper discusses the design and implementation of algorithms for community detection. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category since the paper deals with the complexity of algorithms for community detection and counting. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category since community detection is a common problem in machine learning and the paper discusses the approximation desideratum for community detection.
